HEADWORD: Seigneurial
<hw>Seign*eu"ri*al</hw> <pr>(s⟦emac⟧n*⟦umac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦ait⟧l)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. <ets>seigneur</ets>. See
<er>Seignior</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the lord
of a manor; manorial.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Temple.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Vested with large powers; independent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seignior</ent>⟦br⟧
